                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Archdeacons"><name
                                ref="Becio">Becio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archdeacons">archidiac(o)n(us)</rs>, iubente domno <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/1571">Ioh(anne)s</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">ep(iscopu)s</rs>, accepisse et accepi a vob(is) <persName
                            key="#Priests"><name ref="Albinus">Albin(us)</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">p(res)b(ite)r</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">p(e)n(sionem)</rs> de una <rs key="#Houses"
                            >mansione</rs> cu(m) <rs key="#Landed_possessions">curte</rs> iuxta
                        q(ui) e(st) p(o)s(i)t(a) in regione <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1481"
                            >S(an)c(t)e Marie q(ui) v(ocatur) Fermosa</orgName>, que p(er) <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteusin</rs> tenere viso estis
                        ad iura n(ost)ra <rs key="#Churches">eccl(esi)a</rs>, om(n)iq(ue) ann(o) in
                        vestivitate s(an)c(t)i Cassiani <rs key="#Rent_in_money">p(e)n(sionem)
                            d(e)n(ariorum) III t(an)t(um)</rs>. Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ro feci
                        vob(is) oc deaccepto in m(en)se aug(usto), indic(tione) septima.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
